<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Banking & Finance Exam Practice</title>
<style>
  @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=IBM+Plex+Mono:wght@400;600&family=IBM+Plex+Sans:wght@300;400;500;600&family=IBM+Plex+Serif:ital,wght@0,400;0,600;1,400&display=swap');

  :root {
    --navy: #0B1F3A;
    --navy-mid: #132847;
    --navy-light: #1E3A5F;
    --gold: #C9A84C;
    --gold-light: #E8C96D;
    --cream: #F7F4EE;
    --cream-dark: #EDE8DF;
    --green: #2D6A4F;
    --green-light: #52B788;
    --red: #9B2335;
    --red-light: #D64045;
    --gray: #8C8C8C;
    --text: #1A1A2E;
  }

  * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

  body {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Sans', sans-serif;
    background: var(--cream);
    color: var(--text);
    min-height: 100vh;
  }

  /* ── HEADER ── */
  header {
    background: var(--navy);
    color: white;
    padding: 0;
    position: sticky;
    top: 0;
    z-index: 100;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
  }
  .header-inner {
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 16px 24px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 16px;
  }
  .header-title {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Serif', serif;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    color: var(--gold-light);
  }
  .header-subtitle {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    margin-top: 2px;
  }
  .header-score {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--gold-light);
    text-align: right;
  }

  /* ── TOPIC SELECTOR ── */
  .topic-bar {
    background: var(--navy-mid);
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--gold);
  }
  .topic-bar-inner {
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: flex;
    gap: 0;
  }
  .topic-btn {
    flex: 1;
    padding: 14px 12px;
    background: transparent;
    border: none;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.55);
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.2s;
    border-right: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
    text-align: center;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }
  .topic-btn:last-child { border-right: none; }
  .topic-btn.active {
    background: var(--gold);
    color: var(--navy);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .topic-btn:not(.active):hover {
    background: rgba(201,168,76,0.15);
    color: var(--gold-light);
  }
  .topic-num {
    display: block;
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    opacity: 0.7;
    margin-bottom: 2px;
  }

  /* ── MAIN LAYOUT ── */
  .main {
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 32px 24px;
  }

  /* ── PROGRESS BAR ── */
  .progress-wrap {
    margin-bottom: 28px;
  }
  .progress-meta {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .progress-label {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    color: var(--gray);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  }
  .progress-fraction {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    color: var(--navy);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .progress-bar {
    height: 6px;
    background: var(--cream-dark);
    border-radius: 3px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .progress-fill {
    height: 100%;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--gold), var(--gold-light));
    border-radius: 3px;
    transition: width 0.4s ease;
  }

  /* ── QUESTION CARD ── */
  .question-area { display: none; }
  .question-area.active { display: block; }

  .q-card {
    background: white;
    border-radius: 4px;
    border: 1px solid var(--cream-dark);
    padding: 32px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    box-shadow: 0 1px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
  }
  .q-meta {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    margin-bottom: 18px;
  }
  .q-number {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    color: var(--gold);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  }
  .q-difficulty {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    padding: 3px 10px;
    border-radius: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  }
  .diff-basic { background: #E8F5E9; color: #2D6A4F; }
  .diff-intermediate { background: #FFF8E1; color: #8B6914; }
  .diff-advanced { background: #FDE8E8; color: #9B2335; }

  .q-text {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Serif', serif;
    font-size: 1.08rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  /* ── OPTIONS ── */
  .options { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 10px; }
  .opt-btn {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 14px;
    padding: 14px 18px;
    background: var(--cream);
    border: 2px solid transparent;
    border-radius: 4px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.18s;
    text-align: left;
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .opt-btn:hover:not(:disabled) {
    background: white;
    border-color: var(--gold);
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px var(--gold);
  }
  .opt-letter {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--gray);
    min-width: 20px;
    padding-top: 2px;
    transition: color 0.18s;
  }
  .opt-btn:hover:not(:disabled) .opt-letter { color: var(--gold); }

  .opt-btn.correct {
    background: #EDF7F1;
    border-color: var(--green);
    color: var(--green);
  }
  .opt-btn.correct .opt-letter { color: var(--green); }
  .opt-btn.wrong {
    background: #FDF0F0;
    border-color: var(--red-light);
    color: var(--red);
  }
  .opt-btn.wrong .opt-letter { color: var(--red); }
  .opt-btn.reveal {
    background: #EDF7F1;
    border-color: var(--green);
    color: var(--green);
    opacity: 0.7;
  }
  .opt-btn:disabled { cursor: default; }

  /* ── FEEDBACK ── */
  .feedback {
    margin-top: 20px;
    padding: 16px 20px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    display: none;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .feedback.show { display: block; }
  .feedback.correct-fb {
    background: #EDF7F1;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--green);
    color: #1A4A33;
  }
  .feedback.wrong-fb {
    background: #FDF0F0;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--red-light);
    color: #5C1A1A;
  }
  .feedback strong {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }

  /* ── CONTROLS ── */
  .controls {
    display: flex;
    gap: 12px;
    align-items: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .btn {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: 12px 24px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.18s;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }
  .btn-primary {
    background: var(--navy);
    color: white;
  }
  .btn-primary:hover { background: var(--navy-light); }
  .btn-secondary {
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--navy);
    border: 2px solid var(--navy);
  }
  .btn-secondary:hover { background: var(--navy); color: white; }
  .btn-gold {
    background: var(--gold);
    color: var(--navy);
  }
  .btn-gold:hover { background: var(--gold-light); }
  .btn:disabled {
    opacity: 0.4;
    cursor: default;
  }

  /* ── RESULTS PANEL ── */
  .results-panel {
    display: none;
    background: white;
    border-radius: 4px;
    border: 1px solid var(--cream-dark);
    padding: 40px;
    text-align: center;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
  }
  .results-panel.show { display: block; }
  .results-grade {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Serif', serif;
    font-size: 5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--navy);
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .results-pct {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }
  .results-stats {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 40px;
    margin: 28px 0;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .stat-item { text-align: center; }
  .stat-num {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--navy);
  }
  .stat-label {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--gray);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    margin-top: 4px;
  }
  .results-msg {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Serif', serif;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--text);
    max-width: 460px;
    margin: 0 auto 28px;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* ── QUESTION NAV GRID ── */
  .q-nav {
    margin-top: 28px;
    background: white;
    border: 1px solid var(--cream-dark);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 20px;
  }
  .q-nav-title {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    color: var(--gray);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .q-nav-grid {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 6px;
  }
  .q-dot {
    width: 32px;
    height: 32px;
    border-radius: 3px;
    border: 1px solid var(--cream-dark);
    background: var(--cream);
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    color: var(--gray);
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.15s;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }
  .q-dot:hover { border-color: var(--gold); color: var(--navy); }
  .q-dot.answered-correct { background: #EDF7F1; border-color: var(--green); color: var(--green); }
  .q-dot.answered-wrong { background: #FDF0F0; border-color: var(--red-light); color: var(--red); }
  .q-dot.current { border-color: var(--gold); background: var(--gold); color: var(--navy); font-weight: 700; }

  /* ── AI EXPLAIN BTN ── */
  .ai-btn {
    margin-top: 12px;
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    padding: 8px 16px;
    background: transparent;
    border: 1px solid var(--navy);
    border-radius: 3px;
    color: var(--navy);
    cursor: pointer;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    transition: all 0.18s;
  }
  .ai-btn:hover { background: var(--navy); color: white; }
  .ai-explain-box {
    margin-top: 12px;
    padding: 16px;
    background: var(--cream);
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--text);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--gold);
    display: none;
  }
  .ai-explain-box.show { display: block; }
  .ai-loading {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    color: var(--gray);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
  }
  .spinner {
    width: 14px;
    height: 14px;
    border: 2px solid var(--cream-dark);
    border-top-color: var(--gold);
    border-radius: 50%;
    animation: spin 0.7s linear infinite;
  }
  @keyframes spin { to { transform: rotate(360deg); } }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .main { padding: 20px 16px; }
    .q-card { padding: 22px 18px; }
    .q-text { font-size: 0.97rem; }
    .results-grade { font-size: 3.5rem; }
    .results-stats { gap: 24px; }
    .topic-btn { font-size: 0.68rem; padding: 10px 6px; }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<header>
  <div class="header-inner">
    <div>
      <div class="header-title">Banking &amp; Finance — Exam Practice</div>
      <div class="header-subtitle">Bachelor's Degree · Topics 1–3</div>
    </div>
    <div class="header-score" id="headerScore">Score: — / —</div>
  </div>
  <div class="topic-bar">
    <div class="topic-bar-inner">
      <button class="topic-btn active" onclick="switchTopic(0)">
        <span class="topic-num">TOPIC 1</span>Overview of the Financial Services Sector
      </button>
      <button class="topic-btn" onclick="switchTopic(1)">
        <span class="topic-num">TOPIC 2</span>Financial Statements of Banks
      </button>
      <button class="topic-btn" onclick="switchTopic(2)">
        <span class="topic-num">TOPIC 3</span>Measuring &amp; Evaluating Bank Performance
      </button>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

<div class="main">
  <div class="progress-wrap">
    <div class="progress-meta">
      <span class="progress-label">Progress</span>
      <span class="progress-fraction" id="progressFraction">0 / 0</span>
    </div>
    <div class="progress-bar"><div class="progress-fill" id="progressFill" style="width:0%"></div></div>
  </div>

  <div id="quizArea"></div>
  <div class="results-panel" id="resultsPanel"></div>

  <div class="controls" id="controls" style="margin-top:20px;">
    <button class="btn btn-primary" id="nextBtn" onclick="nextQuestion()" disabled>Next Question →</button>
    <button class="btn btn-secondary" id="prevBtn" onclick="prevQuestion()">← Previous</button>
    <button class="btn btn-gold" id="finishBtn" onclick="showResults()" style="display:none;">Finish &amp; See Results</button>
    <button class="btn btn-secondary" id="restartBtn" onclick="restartTopic()" style="display:none;">Restart Topic</button>
  </div>

  <div class="q-nav" id="qNavPanel">
    <div class="q-nav-title">Question Navigator</div>
    <div class="q-nav-grid" id="qNavGrid"></div>
  </div>
</div>

<script>
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
//  QUESTION BANK  (50+ per topic)
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
const topics = [

// ──────────────── TOPIC 1 ────────────────
{
  title: "Topic 1: Overview of the Financial Services Sector",
  questions: [
    {
      q: "Which of the following best describes the primary role of banks as described in Chapter One?",
      opts: ["To maximize government tax revenues","To serve as the principal source of credit for individuals, families, and units of government","To issue government bonds exclusively","To regulate other financial institutions"],
      ans: 1, diff: "basic",
      expl: "Banks are identified as the principal source of credit (loanable funds) for millions of individuals, families, and many units of government."
    },
    {
      q: "According to the material, U.S. bank assets represent approximately what proportion of total financial assets in the United States?",
      opts: ["One-half","One-quarter","One-fifth","One-third"],
      ans: 2, diff: "basic",
      expl: "The material states that the assets held by U.S. banks represent about one-fifth of total assets, contrasting with other nations where banks often hold half or more."
    },
    {
      q: "Which institution type best fits the description: 'Cover whole regions, nations, and continents and offer the widest possible menu of financial services'?",
      opts: ["Community banks","Cooperative banks","Money-center banks","Credit unions"],
      ans: 2, diff: "basic",
      expl: "Money-center banks (e.g., Maybank, CIMB, HSBC) are described as industry leaders covering whole regions, nations, and continents while offering the widest possible menu of financial services."
    },
    {
      q: "Community banks are characterized by which of the following features?",
      opts: ["They compete globally and acquire smaller businesses","They are much smaller and service local communities with a narrower but often more personalized menu of services","They are exclusively government-owned","They primarily issue international bonds"],
      ans: 1, diff: "basic",
      expl: "Community banks are much smaller, service local communities and towns, and offer a narrower but often more personalized menu of financial services."
    },
    {
      q: "Under U.S. federal law, a bank came to be legally defined primarily by:",
      opts: ["The range of loans it issues","The number of branches it operates","The government agency insuring its deposits (FDIC)","The size of its equity capital"],
      ans: 2, diff: "intermediate",
      expl: "Congress defined a bank as any institution that could qualify for deposit insurance administered by the FDIC; thus, a bank was defined not so much by its service offerings but by its deposit insurer."
    },
    {
      q: "The Financial Services Modernization Act (Gramm-Leach-Bliley Act) of 1999 is significant because it:",
      opts: ["Created the FDIC","Prohibited banks from selling insurance","Allowed many different types of financial firms to offer one-stop shopping for financial services","Banned commercial banks from investment banking"],
      ans: 2, diff: "intermediate",
      expl: "The Gramm-Leach-Bliley Act of 1999 allowed many different types of financial firms to offer the public one-stop shopping for financial services, making it harder to differentiate banks from other financial-service providers."
    },
    {
      q: "Which of the following is NOT listed as a service banks have offered for centuries?",
      opts: ["Carrying out currency exchange","Offering checking accounts","Selling insurance policies","Safekeeping of valuables"],
      ans: 2, diff: "basic",
      expl: "Selling insurance policies is a more recent service banks began offering in the past century. The century-old services include currency exchange, demand deposits, safekeeping of valuables, and trust services."
    },
    {
      q: "Which of the following is a key trend affecting all financial-service firms identified in the material?",
      opts: ["Declining technological innovation","Decreasing competition","Globalization","Reduction in government regulation"],
      ans: 2, diff: "basic",
      expl: "The material lists Globalization as one of the key trends affecting all financial-service firms, along with service proliferation, rising competition, technological change, consolidation, convergence, and others."
    },
    {
      q: "The primary purpose of the financial system, as described in Chapter One, is to:",
      opts: ["Maximize government spending","Encourage savings and transfer those savings to individuals and institutions planning to invest","Regulate currency exchange rates","Provide employment in the banking sector"],
      ans: 1, diff: "basic",
      expl: "The primary purpose of the financial system is to encourage savings and to transfer those savings to individuals and institutions planning to invest and needing credit to do so."
    },
    {
      q: "Which banking legislation in Malaysia replaced the Banking and Financial Institutions Act (BAFIA)?",
      opts: ["Exchange Control Act 1953","Anti Money Laundering Act 2001","Financial Services Act (FSA) 2013","Islamic Financial Institutions Act 2000"],
      ans: 2, diff: "intermediate",
      expl: "The Financial Services Act (FSA) 2013 replaced BAFIA and provides a framework for integrated supervision of the Malaysian financial system."
    },
    {
      q: "Under Malaysian law, the maximum shareholding by an individual in a licensed local financial institution is:",
      opts: ["5%","10%","20%","25%"],
      ans: 1, diff: "intermediate",
      expl: "Under the FSA 2013, individuals are limited to a maximum of 10% shareholding in licensed local financial institutions, while persons other than individuals are limited to 20%."
    },
    {
      q: "The Anti Money Laundering and Anti Terrorism Act 2001 in Malaysia covers which of the following?",
      opts: ["Only the definition of money laundering","Offences, prevention measures, forfeiture of property, and reporting of suspicious transactions","Only reporting requirements for banks","Only penalties for terrorism financing"],
      ans: 1, diff: "intermediate",
      expl: "The Act covers the definition of money laundering, offences under money laundering activities, measures for prevention, forfeiture of property from money laundering activities, and record keeping and reporting of suspicious transactions."
    },
    {
      q: "Which of the following best describes 'fringe banks' as competitors of traditional banks?",
      opts: ["Large multinational financial conglomerates","Non-traditional providers such as payday lenders and check cashers serving underbanked populations","Government-owned savings institutions","Investment banks specializing in securities underwriting"],
      ans: 1, diff: "intermediate",
      expl: "Fringe banks are non-traditional competitors that typically serve underbanked or credit-impaired customers through services like payday lending and check cashing."
    },
    {
      q: "Which of the following financial innovations is associated with banks expanding their service menus in recent decades?",
      opts: ["Restricting services to demand deposits only","Offering investment banking, insurance protection, and financial planning","Eliminating trust services","Reducing cross-border lending"],
      ans: 1, diff: "basic",
      expl: "Bank service menus are expanding rapidly to include investment banking, insurance protection, financial planning, advice for merging companies, risk-management services, and numerous other innovative financial products."
    },
    {
      q: "The Islamic Financial Services Act 2013 in Malaysia will have an impact on which of the following?",
      opts: ["Only Islamic banks","All commercial banks and financial holding companies","The establishment of financial holding companies and limits on shareholding","Only consumer protection laws"],
      ans: 2, diff: "intermediate",
      expl: "The IFSA 2013 affects the establishment/identification of financial holding companies, greater BNM oversight, limits on shareholding, the end of composite licenses, and greater responsibility on consumer protection."
    },
    {
      q: "According to the material, which statement best describes the argument that 'banking is not dying but changing'?",
      opts: ["Banks are losing all their customers to competitors","Banks are offering new services and changing their form to remain competitive","Banks are being fully replaced by fintech companies","Banks are becoming more restrictive in their service offerings"],
      ans: 1, diff: "intermediate",
      expl: "Some experts counter that banking is not dying but changing by offering new services and changing its form, even as traditional banking faces competitive pressure."
    },
    {
      q: "The Exchange Control Act 1953 in Malaysia governs transactions in which areas?",
      opts: ["Only domestic bank loans","Foreign exchange transactions including import/export, capital accounts, foreign direct investments, and portfolio investments","Islamic banking operations only","Consumer credit protection"],
      ans: 1, diff: "intermediate",
      expl: "The Exchange Control Act 1953 governs conduct of foreign exchange transactions including current accounts (import/export), capital accounts, foreign direct investments, investment abroad by residents, foreign credit facilities, portfolio investments, and Ringgit credit facilities."
    },
    {
      q: "Which of the following is a 'supporting service' provided by the financial system in addition to its primary purpose?",
      opts: ["Issuing government bonds","Payment services, risk protection services, and liquidity services","Setting national interest rates","Printing currency"],
      ans: 1, diff: "basic",
      expl: "The financial system provides supporting services including payment services, risk protection services, and liquidity services, in addition to its primary role of encouraging savings and directing investment."
    },
    {
      q: "A Loan Officer, Credit Analyst, and Trust Department Specialist are examples of what?",
      opts: ["Types of bank competitors","Career opportunities in banking and financial services","Types of financial instruments","Regulatory positions"],
      ans: 1, diff: "basic",
      expl: "These are examples of the different kinds of professionals who work inside financial firms, as listed in the Appendix on Career Opportunities in Banking and Financial Services."
    },
    {
      q: "Which of the following best describes 'convergence' as a trend in financial services?",
